<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
<title>The God Test — Chapter One</title>

<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Cormorant+Garamond:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

<style>
    :root{
        --bg:#f6f3ef;
        --paper:#fffdf9;
        --ink:#1f1f1f;
        --muted:#6d6d6d;
        --accent:#1d4c8f;
        --gold:#c89b47;
        --line:#ddd7cf;
    }

    *{
        margin:0;
        padding:0;
        box-sizing:border-box;
    }

    body{
        background:linear-gradient(to bottom,#efebe6,#f8f5f1);
        color:var(--ink);
        font-family:'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
        line-height:1.8;
        padding:60px 20px;
    }

    .page{
        max-width:1200px;
        margin:auto;
        background:var(--paper);
        border-radius:18px;
        box-shadow:
            0 10px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.08),
            0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
        overflow:hidden;
    }

    .hero{
        padding:80px 90px 60px;
        border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);
        position:relative;
    }

    .chapter-label{
        text-align:center;
        letter-spacing:4px;
        font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;
        font-size:14px;
        font-weight:600;
        color:var(--accent);
        margin-bottom:18px;
    }

    .title{
        text-align:center;
        font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;
        font-size:clamp(3rem,7vw,6rem);
        font-weight:700;
        line-height:0.95;
        letter-spacing:-3px;
        color:#163a6b;
        text-transform:uppercase;
    }

    .divider{
        width:120px;
        height:2px;
        background:var(--gold);
        margin:35px auto 0;
    }

    .content{
        display:grid;
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0,1fr) 320px;
        gap:60px;
        padding:70px 90px 90px;
    }

    .main{
        font-size:1.55rem;
    }

    .main p{
        margin-bottom:32px;
    }

    .main p:first-child::first-letter{
        float:left;
        font-size:6rem;
        line-height:0.8;
        padding-right:12px;
        font-weight:600;
        color:var(--accent);
    }

    .sidebar{
        display:flex;
        flex-direction:column;
        gap:30px;
    }

    .quote-box{
        border-left:4px solid var(--gold);
        padding-left:24px;
    }

    .quote-mark{
        font-size:4rem;
        color:var(--gold);
        line-height:1;
        margin-bottom:10px;
    }

    .quote{
        font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;
        font-size:1.4rem;
        line-height:1.6;
        color:#173b6f;
        font-weight:500;
    }

    .info-card{
        background:#f2f5fa;
        border:1px solid #dbe4f2;
        padding:30px;
        border-radius:16px;
    }

    .info-card h3{
        font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;
        font-size:0.95rem;
        letter-spacing:2px;
        color:var(--accent);
        margin-bottom:18px;
        text-transform:uppercase;
    }

    .info-card p{
        font-size:1.25rem;
        line-height:1.7;
    }

    .section-heading{
        margin-top:70px;
        margin-bottom:24px;
        font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;
        text-transform:uppercase;
        font-size:1.3rem;
        letter-spacing:2px;
        color:var(--accent);
        border-top:2px solid var(--gold);
        padding-top:18px;
    }

    .callout{
        margin:45px 0;
        background:#fbf7ef;
        border:1px solid #eadfca;
        padding:35px;
        border-radius:18px;
    }

    .callout-title{
        font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;
        font-size:1rem;
        letter-spacing:2px;
        text-transform:uppercase;
        color:#9a6b1e;
        margin-bottom:15px;
    }

    .callout p{
        margin:0;
        font-size:1.35rem;
    }

    .footer{
        padding:30px 90px 50px;
        border-top:1px solid var(--line);
        font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;
        color:var(--muted);
        font-size:0.95rem;
        display:flex;
        justify-content:space-between;
        align-items:center;
    }

    .page-number{
        color:var(--accent);
        font-weight:700;
        font-size:1.1rem;
    }

    @media (max-width: 960px){

        .content{
            grid-template-columns:1fr;
            padding:50px 35px 60px;
        }

        .hero{
            padding:60px 35px 40px;
        }

        .footer{
            padding:30px 35px 45px;
        }

        .main{
            font-size:1.35rem;
        }

        .title{
            letter-spacing:-1px;
        }
    }
</style>
</head>

<body>

<div class="page">

    <section class="hero">
        <div class="chapter-label">
            CHAPTER ONE
        </div>

        <h1 class="title">
            A Blast From<br>
            The Future
        </h1>

        <div class="divider"></div>
    </section>

    <section class="content">

        <article class="main">

            <p>
                In 1983, while researching an article about artificial intelligence
                for <em>The Wilson Quarterly</em>, Robert Wright interviewed an
                obscure computer scientist named Geoffrey Hinton. At the time,
                Hinton advocated an unconventional approach to AI — one many
                researchers dismissed as fringe.
            </p>

            <p>
                Four decades later, Hinton would become known as “The Godfather
                of AI.” The very methods he championed eventually led to dramatic
                breakthroughs in generative artificial intelligence: systems capable
                of producing images, text, code, and conversation with startling fluency.
            </p>

            <div class="callout">
                <div class="callout-title">
                    The Shift
                </div>

                <p>
                    AI was no longer a distant laboratory curiosity. It had entered
                    everyday life — and with it came excitement, anxiety, speculation,
                    and fear about what humanity had unleashed.
                </p>
            </div>

            <p>
                Hinton himself became increasingly alarmed by the speed of progress.
                AI systems were improving far faster than expected, raising concerns
                about misinformation, job displacement, autonomous decision-making,
                and eventually the possibility of machines acting independently
                of human interests.
            </p>

            <h2 class="section-heading">
                Which Awe Is In Order?
            </h2>

            <p>
                Wright frames the public reaction to AI as existing along an “awe
                spectrum.” On one side are the accelerationists — those who see AI
                as the gateway to abundance, medical miracles, and post-scarcity
                civilization. On the other are the doomers, who imagine humanity
                surrendering power to superintelligent systems.
            </p>

            <p>
                Between those extremes lies a more difficult question:
                can humanity guide technological evolution wisely enough
                to preserve freedom, meaning, and moral agency?
            </p>

        </article>

        <aside class="sidebar">

            <div class="quote-box">
                <div class="quote-mark">“</div>

                <div class="quote">
                    The approach he championed had worked.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="info-card">
                <h3>
                    Generative AI
                </h3>

                <p>
                    AI systems that generate text, images, audio,
                    code, or simulations based on patterns learned
                    from enormous datasets.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="info-card">
                <h3>
                    The Singularity
                </h3>

                <p>
                    A hypothetical point where AI improves itself
                    recursively, causing an explosive acceleration
                    in intelligence and technological change.
                </p>
            </div>

        </aside>

    </section>

    <footer class="footer">
        <div>
            Inspired by <em>The God Test</em> by Robert Wright
        </div>

        <div class="page-number">
            — 01 —
        </div>
    </footer>

</div>

</body>
</html>

